<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><table-reference author="Kieran O'Donnell" dateTime="2021-03-04T10:37:23" graph="None" id="_acc16a05-f30a-4bff-8598-a1c5a608e57d" type="insert"><num>5.3.3</num><title id="_6cb0db50-8cd3-4721-9c27-07d1ce758b97">Spacing of return walls for cavity walls with openings — distance from the edge of an opening (mm)</title><table id="_496c73b6-bc8c-4c0c-8c93-d3176f491cde" keycol="1"><tgroup cols="5"><colspec colname="001" colnum="1" colwidth="86.40*"/><colspec colname="002" colnum="2" colwidth="86.40*"/><colspec colname="003" colnum="3" colwidth="86.40*"/><colspec colname="004" colnum="4" colwidth="86.40*"/><colspec colname="005" colnum="5" colwidth="86.40*"/><thead><row><entry morerows="1">Wind class</entry><entry nameend="005" namest="002">Opening width (mm)</entry></row><row><entry>900</entry><entry>1500</entry><entry>2100</entry><entry>2700</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>N3</entry><entry>2100</entry><entry>1800</entry><entry>800</entry><entry>400</entry></row><row><entry>N2</entry><entry>3200</entry><entry>2900</entry><entry>2600</entry><entry>2300</entry></row><row><entry>N1</entry><entry>2500<sup id="_2720b8f1-07a9-4fd0-a05f-93b8c61ac174">(Note)</sup></entry><entry>2200<sup id="_62f08ba1-f7e9-4d71-a4e8-b065000ee842">(Note)</sup></entry><entry>1900<sup id="_25fa16ad-bff4-424f-a65b-6c625840ab84">(Note)</sup></entry><entry>800<sup id="_ba1ccb41-3e87-4803-88c8-ad87728704ed">(Note)</sup></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><desc-note id="_d2d01991-3a12-436a-b71a-80bf9357c798"><p>The spacing in wind class N1 is smaller than for N2 because <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1163_1.15.0.xml#_41819054-c79b-4319-ad36-223fccb70f02" id="_8bca2731-fe8e-49df-9b1e-a30543ab496f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">5.6.5</xref> states that for <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1214_0.10.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_74fe83e6-5d66-4484-9104-e0dc1dd35c38" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> walls in wind class N1, light duty <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1214_0.10.0.xml#_d9f8479e-3794-41cf-ab60-e1588241810e" id="_80e6c23f-aa4c-4149-ab6b-881eed3e646d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">cavity</xref> ties are to be used. This results in only relying on one leaf to resist the load instead of sharing it equally as per clause 7.7.3 of AS 3700.</p></desc-note></table-reference>